      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h3>GroupPicker widget</h3>
        It takes a standard input textfield and adds a modal window to it. The modal window allows you to search for groups by username or actual name.
        
        <h3>Options</h3>
        The call can be made to either <code>group_picker</code> or <code>group_multi_picker</code> depending on if you want to allow multiple groups to be selected.
        
        <h3>Code</h3>
        <h4>View code</h4>
        <pre>from ....core.system.js_widgets import GroupPicker

def view_function(request):
    GroupPicker(request)</pre>
    
        <h4>HTML code</h4>
        It varies from widget to widget, here is the user picker
        <pre><strong style="font-size:1.1em;">Single picker</strong>
&lt;div class="input-group"&gt;
  &lt;span class="input-group-addon btn-info btn" onclick="group_picker('#group_search');"&gt;
    &lt;i class="fa fa-users fa-fw"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;input type="text" class="form-control" id="group_search" name="group_name" placeholder="" /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

<strong style="font-size:1.1em;">Multi picker</strong>
&lt;div class="input-group"&gt;
  &lt;span class="input-group-addon btn-info btn" onclick="group_multi_picker('#group_search');"&gt;
    &lt;i class="fa fa-users fa-fw"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;input type="text" class="form-control" id="group_search" name="group_name" placeholder="" /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</pre>


      <h4>Form processing code</h4>
      user_f.find_groups
      user_f.search_multiuser_string


      </div>
    </div>
